# -*- mode:org; -*-

* settings.el - manage system settings in Emacs

*settings.el* is a simple Emacs UI for managing system settings. It provides the
=M-x settings= GUI control panel. The interface consists of folding sections
that are visually inspired by Org-mode and Magit.

The latest release can control:
- display mirroring
- audio volume and muting
# - network connections (WiFi)

** Platform support matrix

| OS      | Audio | Monitors |
|---------+-------+----------|
| Linux   | Y     | Y        |
| MacOS   | Y     | N        |
| Windows | N     | N        |

** Install

You can install the latest version using =M-x package-vc-install=, available in
Emacs 30.1 or later.

#+begin_example
  M-x package-vc-install RET https://github.com/hufoe/settings.el
#+end_example

Or add this to your =.emacs=:
#+begin_src emacs-lisp
    (use-package settings :vc (:url "https://github.com/hufoe/settings.el"))
#+end_src

Then run the command =M-x settings= to start the GUI.

** Dependencies

To manage system settings on Linux, the following programs must be installed:
- =xrandr=: for monitors
- =pactl= (part of =pulseaudio-utils=): for audio
# - =nmcli=: for networking
